HOW TO PUT THE APP ONLINE AS A WEBAPP
(Do these in order. Everything here is free to start.)

The 3 websites you'll sign up for:
    - GitHub (github.com) -> stores your code online
    - Supabase (supabase.com) -> the backend (accounts, logins, database)
    - Vercel (vercel.com) -> hosting (this is what actually puts the website on the internet)

1. Put your code on GitHub (your code's online home)
    - Make a free account at github.com
    - Download GitHub Desktop from desktop.github.com (this lets you upload code without typing commands)
    - Open GitHub Desktop -> File -> Add Local Repository -> pick your "taskteen" folder
    - Click "Publish repository" (you can keep it Private)
    - Done -> your code now lives on GitHub, and you "Push" to it whenever you make changes

2. Set up Supabase (your backend)
    - Make a free account at supabase.com
    - Click "New Project" -> name it -> pick the region closest to you -> set a database password (save it somewhere safe)
    - Wait about 2 minutes for it to finish building
    - Go to Project Settings -> API and copy these TWO things:
        - Project URL
        - anon public key
        - (NEVER copy or share the "service_role" secret key - that one stays private)
    - Keep these two handy, Vercel needs them in the next step
    - NOTE: the app's code still has to be wired to Supabase for real logins/data to work across devices. That's the coding part, I can do that for you. Until then the live site works like the demo (accounts saved per device).

3. Set up Vercel (this puts the website online)
    - Make a free account at vercel.com -> choose "Continue with GitHub" so they connect automatically
    - Click "Add New" -> "Project"
    - Find your "taskteen" repository in the list -> click Import
    - Set these build settings:
        - Framework Preset -> Other
        - Build Command -> npx expo export -p web
        - Output Directory -> dist
    - Add these Environment Variables (paste in the two things from step 2):
        - Name: EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL        Value: (your Project URL)
        - Name: EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY   Value: (your anon public key)
    - Click "Deploy" and wait ~2 minutes
    - You get a free live link like your-app.vercel.app -> that's your website, it's now online!

4. Add one small file so pages don't break on refresh
    - Without this, refreshing a page (like the profile page) can show an error
    - It's a tiny file called "vercel.json" that tells the site to always load correctly
    - I can create this file for you in 2 seconds, just ask

5. (Optional) Use your own website name instead of ....vercel.app
    - Buy a domain name from Namecheap.com, Cloudflare.com, or GoDaddy.com (example: getsidekick.com)
    - In Vercel -> your Project -> Settings -> Domains -> type your domain -> follow the steps it shows
    - The secure padlock / HTTPS is added automatically for free

6. How to update the live site later (super easy)
    - Make your changes in the code
    - Open GitHub Desktop -> click "Commit" -> then "Push"
    - Vercel automatically notices and rebuilds the website in ~2 minutes
    - No other steps, it updates itself

QUICK RECAP OF WHAT CONNECTS TO WHAT:
    - GitHub holds the code
    - Vercel pulls the code from GitHub and builds the website
    - Vercel talks to Supabase (using the 2 keys) for accounts and data
    - You push to GitHub -> Vercel auto-updates the live site

(Note: turning this into phone apps for the iPhone App Store / Google Play is a
separate process with different tools and accounts. This checklist is just for
the website version.)
